<br>
Take away Paladin's mana free super aggro stuns and you'll be seeing a lot more med breaks needed to pull the stuff off they're doing, and that'll be balanced since they might have super aggro but the group as a whole needs to slow down and wait for them.<br>
<br>
Paladins should MT when you're in an area that's so hard that you can't afford to mess up, not because everyone is too lazy and want to tank the mob.  Of course, if you're in an area that's so hard that no one can mess up at all, it's usually better to relocate to somewhere else easier anyway. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raunstoncutter>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 336<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/20/03 3:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2930.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: From the clerics...</span><hr size=1> In my PoV/PoS experience, I usually haven't had a problem tanking and maintaining agro.  I have my own method, which usually don't get anyone killed.  Although, the slowers just have to accept that they will take a couple hits during the fight, and most people that I group with (mostly pick ups) are fine with that.  My clerics pretty rarely go OOM or LOM healing me and the occasional beat down for the other class.<br>
<br>
Actually, here's a funny story.  I was in Inner Caves in PoV the other day, and I had been tanking for a good long while.  My monk asked me what stun I was using to keep agro.  I told him I was a warrior.  Go figure, a dwarf in plate with a windblade.  He was pretty impressed that I was able to hold agro as well (at 61) as I did since our previous 65 warrior had a bit more trouble.<br>
<br>
A lot of agro management has to do with people playing their class.  If they are good, then anyone can tank.  If they are sloppy and lazy, then they need someone to make their style easier.  I'm glad I can tank, and I'm glad the knights don't feel so left behind.<br>
<br>
